: Holarctic. 
<number box="[485,513,1152,1176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="13.0">13</number>
species (some still undescribed) known from North 
<collectingCountry box="[1129,1226,1151,1176]" name="United States of America" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">America</collectingCountry>
and an additional species collected at a high elevation (
<quantity box="[616,712,1188,1212]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="3200.0">3200 m</quantity>
) in 
<collectingCountry box="[772,857,1188,1213]" name="Mexico" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mexico</collectingCountry>
State, 
<collectingCountry box="[950,1035,1188,1213]" name="Mexico" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(Cook 1976, 1980). One species widespread in Western, Central and Southern Europe and one species from South 
<collectingCountry box="[1069,1114,1224,1247]" name="Iran" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Iran</collectingCountry>
(Asadi and Pešić 
<number box="[1316,1377,1224,1248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2010.0">2010</number>
).
